{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"51013837-0ddc-474b-a0d1-5a871a89a178","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException<T>` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws<T>` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName);\n}\n```\n\n**Why modernize:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs (e.g., the constructor could throw instead of `CreateUser`)\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pinpoints the exact call and lets you inspect the exception (message, properties, inner exception)\n- The test fails properly if no exception is thrown","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9e206401-0858-4042-8b3f-c8552671a031","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":256,"requestId":"0C01:381B5A:3D6C47:475BCC:69F00D02"},"id":"99370af5-26fc-4cf2-9a4d-a61718754b94","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:27:37.496Z","parentId":"76fd25d2-3892-4788-893f-e7761cddec1f"}
